                                <!-- Project Details Go Here -->
								<h2>Robot Ball</h2>
								<br>
								<div class="img-responsive img-centered"> <!-- class="preview" align="center"> -->
									<img name="preview3" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/r1.jpg" alt=""/>
								</div>
								<div class="thumbnails" align ="center">
									<img onmouseover="preview3.src=img9.src" name="img9" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/r1.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="preview3.src=img10.src" name="img10" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/r2.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="preview3.src=img11.src" name="img11" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/r3.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="preview3.src=img12.src" name="img12" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/r4.jpg" alt=""/>
								</div> 
									<br><br>
								<h3>Role:</h3>
								<p>Robot Ball is a time based puzzle/platformer game which I designed and developed using the Unreal Engine. The idea is you play as a robot that is about to self destruct. You must complete the level before this happens. The robot can also be damaged by lasers and other traps which will speed up the self destruction. The game consists of two levels and a bonus level. </p>
								<br>
								<div class="imagespacing"><embed width="640" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/LsdNByajUUA" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></div>
								<br>
								<h3>How to Play:</h3>
								<p>Use 'W', 'A', 'S', 'D' (WASD) or the arrow keys to move the robot. Reach the exit room before you run out of time or your health hits zero.
								Use the mouse to control the camera location.</p>
								<h3>Citations:</h3>
								<p>All of the art assets were provided through the Scifi Hallway pack in the Epic Games store. The BB8 character model, and audio were also a free to use downloads.
								I made the skysphere by following a tutorial that uses a software called Skyscape. 
								</p>
                                <ul class="list-inline">
                                    <li>Date: February 2016</li>
                                    <li>Software: Unreal Engine 4</li>
                                    <li>Category: Games</li>
                                </ul>
                                <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal"><i class="fa fa-times"></i> Close Project</button>
