                                <!-- Project Details Go Here -->
                                <h2>Super Stop Mario Bros.</h2>
								<br>
								<div class="imagespacing"><embed width="640" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/WYWv1-X-3yE" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></div>
								<br>
								<h3>Role:</h3>
								<p>This was a passion project so I was responsible for majority of the work. I created the story boards as well as all of the art that would be in the project. I brought in some friends to assist me with the lighting, production, and capturing the images. Once the project was on camera, I used Adobe Photoshop and Premiere Pro to form the images into a stop motion video.</p>								
								<br>
								<div class="img-responsive img-centered"> <!-- class="preview" align="center"> -->
									<img name="previews" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/m1.jpg" alt=""/>
								</div>
								<div class="thumbnails" align ="center">
									<img onmouseover="previews.src=img5.src" name="img5" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/m1.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="previews.src=img6.src" name="img6" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/m2.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="previews.src=img7.src" name="img7" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/m3.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="previews.src=img8.src" name="img8" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/m4.jpg" alt=""/>
								</div> 
								<br>
								<h3>Overview:</h3>
								<p>This is a stop motion animation project I created. The project plays through a level of the Super Mario Bros. with a few twists. I only used sticky notes and construction paper to create the characters and scenery.</p>
                                <ul class="list-inline">
                                    <li>Date: December 2013</li>
                                    <li>Software: Adobe CS6</li>
                                    <li>Category: Animation</li>
                                </ul>
