                            <div class="modal-body">
                                <!-- Project Details Go Here -->
                                <h2>Medical Simulations</h2>
								<br>	
								<div class="imagespacing"><embed width="640" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/-LxOHiRtStU" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></div>
								<h3>Role:</h3>
								<p>As a Technical Designer, I develop medical simulations that allow surgeons to practice with haptic feedback in a virtual operating room (OR). I am responsible for developing the medical simulations utilizing our in house haptic API and OR UI. Additionally I integrate user feedback and create videos to be used as marketing content.
								</p>
								<br>
								<h3>Stereognosis</h3>
								<div class="imagespacing"><embed width="640" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Ce2FNyoFem0" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></div>
								<br>
								<h3>Description:</h3>
								<p>The simulation used in the video above is known as a Stereognosis. Its purpose is for doctors to test their sense of feel so that they can better deduce what parts of the body they are interacting with during surgery. The version I developed uses a scoring system to track the users performance. Additionally, the difficulty in telling which ball is the softest also increases.</p>
                                <h3>Ventriculostomy</h3>
								<div class="imagespacing"><embed width="640" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Q346RUiBEow" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></div>
								<br>
								<h3>Description:</h3>
								<p>The goal of a Ventriculostomy is for surgeons to drain liquid from the cerebral ventricles in the brain. To complete this simulation, the user must properly place the catheter in the ventricles after creating an incision and drilling an opening in the skull. Using the haptic pen allows the user to get the proper feel of where the catheter is while it is inside of the brain.</p>  
								<ul class="list-inline">
                                    <li>Date: October 2017</li>
                                    <li>Software: Unity</li>
                                    <li>Category: Simulation</li>
                                </ul>
                                <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal"><i class="fa fa-times"></i> Close Project</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
