                                <!-- Project Details Go Here -->
                                <h2>Night Journey</h2>
								<br>	
								<div class="img-responsive img-centered">
									<img name="preview6" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/n4.jpg" alt=""/>
								</div>
								<div class="thumbnails" align ="center">
									<img onmouseover="preview6.src=img21.src" name="img21" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/n1.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="preview6.src=img22.src" name="img22" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/n2.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="preview6.src=img23.src" name="img23" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/n3.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="preview6.src=img24.src" name="img24" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/n4.jpg" alt=""/>
								</div>
								<h3>Role:</h3>
								<p>Night Journey is a project I design and developed using the Unreal Engine. I developed this project over 5 weeks for a class project. Part of my goal for this project was to create a level using the procedural foliage tool in the Unreal Engine. Many of the assets used were downloaded from the Unreal Engine marketplace. In this game you play as a thief who lives in a magical forest. In the forest there are travelers and creatures that you will encounter. Your interactions and items you find within the environment determine the fate of the characters at the end of the night.</p>
								<br>
								<div class="imagespacing"><embed width="640" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/QghHLTmBrJs" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></div>
								<br>
								<h3>How to Play:</h3>
								<p>Use 'W', 'A', 'S', 'D' (WASD) to move and the mouse to look around. Pressing: 'I' will open up your inventory,'E' will allow you to interact with the environment, and 'Q' will toggle your flashlight on and off. You can also hold down 'Shift' to sprint.</p>
                                <ul class="list-inline">
                                    <li>Date: December 2015</li>
                                    <li>Software: Unreal Engine 4</li>
                                    <li>Category: Games</li>
                                </ul>
