                                <h2>GrayScale</h2>
								<br>	
								<div class="img-responsive img-centered">
									<img name="preview8" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/g4.jpg" alt=""/>
								</div>
								<div class="thumbnails" align ="center">
									<img onmouseover="preview8.src=img29.src" name="img29" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/g1.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="preview8.src=img30.src" name="img30" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/g2.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="preview8.src=img31.src" name="img31" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/g3.jpg" alt=""/>
									<img onmouseover="preview8.src=img32.src" name="img32" src="img/portfolio/fullsize/g4.jpg" alt=""/>
								</div>
								<h3>Role:</h3>
								<p>GrayScale is a tower-defense game where I worked as team leader and game designer. The goal of the game is to protect your "Hero" from the waves of enemies that appear on the screen. There are 10 levels and a boss battle to the game. Aside from my main roles, I also worked on the sound, aesthetics, and the opening scene for the game.</p>
								<br>
								<div class="imagespacing"><embed width="640" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Jvbrv4VwQhU" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></div>
								<br>
								<h3>How to Play:</h3>
								<p>Use the mouse to protect the "Hero" from the waves of enemies. The left click can be used to select items on the bottom of the screen that you can use to deviate the enemies. The right click can be used to "erase" enemies. There are meters on the top right of the screen that deplete as you use the mouse. Use strategy to find the best way to manage your resources and survive.</p>
                                <ul class="list-inline">
                                    <li>Date: April 2013</li>
                                    <li>Software: XNA</li>
                                    <li>Category: Games</li>
                                </ul>
