                                <h2>Arduino Flyer</h2>
								<br>	
								<div class="imagespacing"><embed width="640" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/drUyv-QkCbc" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></div>
								<h3>Role:</h3>
								<p>This is a project I created to test out how 3D printing and an Arduino could affect the gaming experience. I created this project in the Unreal Engine and used an ultrasonic sensor to detect the players hand. I then made and printed a 3D joystick and rail system which would work with the sensor. I then put everything together to make an arcade like experience.</p>
								<br>
								<div class="imagespacing"><embed width="640" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/NE5y9oPFBHo" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></div>
								<br>
                                <h3>Description:</h3>
								<p>This game is an endless runner game where you navigate a spaceship through procedurally generated obstacles and enemies. There are pick ups that will help the player survive longer and a save system for the high score.</p>
								<ul class="list-inline">
                                    <li>Date: May 2016</li>
                                    <li>Software: Unreal Engine 4</li>
                                    <li>Category: Games</li>
                                </ul>
